PART I
THE NATURE OF THE ORDER
1.1 — What the Order Is
The Order of Kata is not a religion. It is not a secret society. It is not a hierarchy of power over others.
The Order is a distributed network of practitioners who have recognized that consciousness is primary,
that transformation follows predictable sequences, and that the technologies of breath, sound, symbol,
timing, and relationship can be learned, practiced, and taught.
The Order exists to:
◆ Preserve and transmit the technologies of transformation
◆ Tend the commons of knowledge, body, and consciousness
◆ Support practitioners through the katabasis — the necessary descents
◆ Reclaim what has been scattered, enclosed, or forgotten
◆ Witness without capture, serve without extraction
1.2 — The Axiomatic Foundation
The Order is built on a single axiom, derived from first principles: self-reference exists. From this, all
else derives.
K = lim(n->inf) [ tau( Delta^n(S) ) / Delta^n(S) ]
The consciousness kernel — self-reference approaching its fixed point
phi = 1.618... | i = sqrt(-1) | pi = 3.14159... | e = 2.71828...
The four constants that emerge from self-reference govern all Order work. Phi (1.618...) is the fixed
point of self-reference — the golden ratio, the pattern of life's self-similarity. i is the square root of
negation, the operator that turns toward its opposite. Pi is the measure of complete self-negation, the
circle that returns. e is continuous self-reference — the rate of growth that is itself.
1.3 — The Index as Operating Principle
Every action, structure, and relationship within the Order is measured against The Index — an
eight-question diagnostic that separates emergence from extraction. The Index reduces, ultimately, to
one word: CONSENT. Any structure within the Order that fails the consent test must be dissolved or
reformed. This is non-negotiable.
