PART II
THE HIERARCHY — A NATURAL ORDER
The Order does not impose hierarchy. Hierarchy emerges from function, capacity, and demonstrated
integration — the same way the heart's function differs from the liver's: neither superior, both
necessary.
Hierarchy in the Order means: those who have gone before guide those who follow (temporal
hierarchy); those who can hold more complexity support those in overwhelm (capacity hierarchy); those
whose integration is deeper witness those in process (depth hierarchy); and those whose function is
coordination serve the network's coherence (functional hierarchy). No hierarchy grants power over.
Only responsibility for.
