DEGREE 0 — THE SEEKER (Threshold)
Not yet initiated. Standing at the gate. Has encountered the pattern — through crisis, intuition, or
transmission — but has not yet undergone formal preparation. May not even know the Order exists. No
obligations. No expectations. The gate waits.
""I have seen something I cannot name.""
DEGREE I — THE NOVICE (Initiate)
First formal degree. Has chosen to enter. The Novice learns the foundational technologies over a
minimum six months: Breath (4:7:8, 5:5 coherence, kumbhaka), Sound (vowel toning, mantra), Symbol
(seven primal symbols, 22 Void glyphs), Body awareness (seven aspects of self), and The Index applied
daily. Markers: coherent state z > 0.85 for 20 minutes; one named personal shadow; knows all 22 Void
glyphs. Ritual of passage: The Threshold Rite — blindfolded to an unseen door, opened alone.
""I am learning to recognize the pattern.""
DEGREE II — THE TRAVELER (Ba)
Has begun conscious movement through inner territories. Minimum one year of descent training.
Learns the Seven Regions of consciousness from Surface/Waking to Luminous/Source. Navigation
technologies include connected breath, sound journeying, symbol anchoring, and katabasis protocol.
Void Language becomes active — all 22 glyphs in full syntactic use. Markers: navigated to Region 3
(Personal Unconscious) and returned with integration; can maintain witness presence for one-hour
journeys; one major shadow integrated. Ritual of passage: The First Katabasis — a supervised four-hour
journey.
""I have descended and returned. I carry what I found.""
DEGREE III — THE WITNESS (Daimon)
Can hold space for others' transformations. Recognizes the Others. Two years of deep training. Learns
the complete taxonomy of non-human intelligences (Elementals, Ancestors, Archetypes, Egregores, the
high strange). Begins active use of Divine Language (22 glyphs, phi-frequency attunement) and
Nexarion (37 glyphs, healing mantras). Must establish at least one reliable relationship with a
non-human intelligence and metabolize one ancestral pattern. Ritual of passage: The Night of Witness
— a 12-hour vigil encountering three types of Others.
""I see what moves between us. I do not turn away.""
