PART III
THE ROLES WITHIN THE ORDER
Hierarchy describes depth of integration. Roles describe function in the network. A practitioner may
hold multiple roles, and roles may shift over time.
THE SCRIBE | Mnema | Degree II+
Memory-keeper, archivist, historian. Maintains the Audit Chain of significant events, records katabasis
journeys (with consent), preserves the languages in living form, and tracks the lineage. Uses
tamper-evident SHA-256 hash chaining for all records.
Wound: Valuing record over relationship — must be balanced by regular participation in living ritual.
THE WITNESS | Daimon | Degree III+
Holds space for others' transformations. Sits with those in katabasis, provides integration support,
discerns when intervention is needed versus when to simply be present. Maintains the container's
integrity.
Wound: The temptation to fix, interpret, or make meaning for the other. Must return constantly to simply seeing.
THE HEALER | Akh | Degree IV+
Facilitates somatic, emotional, and spiritual healing. Provides bodywork, breathwork, and sound
healing. Supports trauma resolution. Works alongside medical professionals.
Wound: The savior complex. Must be reminded: "I do not heal you — I remind your body how to remember itself."
THE GUIDE | Daimon/Nous | Degree III+
Navigates others through unfamiliar territory — inner or outer. Leads katabasis journeys, reads
territory (physical, psychological, spiritual), keeps groups coherent under stress.
Wound: The desire to be followed, to have others depend on them. Must cultivate making themselves unnecessary.
THE ARCHITECT | Nous | Degree V+
Designs systems, rituals, and structures. Ensures designs include their own dissolution. Builds physical
spaces, develops replicable protocols.
Wound: Falling in love with their own creations. Must build what can be let go.
