Principles of Permissible Force
Proportionality: The force used must be proportional to the threat.
Necessity: Force may only be used when all other options have failed.
Accountability: Every use of force must be witnessed and recorded in the Audit Chain.
Consent: Even in defense, the defender's consent to engage must be clear.
Cease-fire: The moment the threat ends, force must end.
Healing: After force is used, the Healers attend to all parties — including the aggressor, if possible.
