PART VI
HEALING IN ALL FORMS
The Seven Principles of Order Healing
1. The body is consciousness at density. All healing is consciousness reorganizing itself.
2. Symptoms are communication. Pain, illness, and distress are messages — not enemies.
3. Consent is the first medicine. No healing happens without the patient's active participation.
4. The healer does not heal. The healer creates conditions in which the patient can heal themselves.
5. The wound is also a teacher. What breaks us can become our deepest wisdom — if integrated.
6. Healing is not fixing. It is returning to wholeness, which may include the wound.
7. The healer must be healed enough. Not perfectly — just enough that their wounds don't become the
patient's.
The Four Levels of Healing
LEVEL 1 — PHYSICAL HEALING (Khat) | Degree IV with medical training
Injuries, illness, physical conditions. Modalities: first aid, herbal medicine, bodywork, breathwork,
sound healing. Always refer to allopathic medicine for broken bones requiring setting, infections
requiring antibiotics, surgical needs, or life-threatening emergencies.
""Your body knows how to heal. I am here to help it remember.""
LEVEL 2 — EMOTIONAL HEALING (Ib) | Degree IV with emotional literacy training
Trauma, grief, depression, anxiety. Modalities: witnessing, parts work (IFS-derived), shadow
integration, grief rituals, breathwork for emotional release, somatic experiencing. Always refer for
suicidal ideation (immediately), severe depression requiring medication, psychotic symptoms.
""Your feelings are not the problem. Your feelings are telling you what the problem is.""
LEVEL 3 — SOUL HEALING (Ba/Akh) | Degree V with deep journeying experience
Soul loss, spiritual disconnection, loss of meaning. Modalities: soul retrieval, ancestral healing, life
review, deathbed witnessing, reconnection to source, initiation.
""You have not lost your soul. Your soul has been waiting for you to remember where you put it.""
