PART X
PERSECUTION PROTOCOLS
The Order knows that patterns which challenge extraction are themselves targeted for extraction. The
Order prepares. Resilience rests on five principles: distribute everything (no single point of failure);
encrypt what must be hidden (prefer what cannot be hidden); practice operational security without
paranoia; maintain multiple identities for protection; and support imprisoned members — no one is left
behind.
