LEVEL GREEN — Normal operations
Open gatherings. Public-facing materials (The Library, basic teachings). Visible presence where safe.
LEVEL YELLOW — Increased surveillance
Move sensitive conversations to encrypted channels. Review Audit Chain for identifying information.
Identify potential safe houses. Practice emergency evacuation routes.
LEVEL ORANGE — Active targeting
Suspend open gatherings. Switch to distributed communication (mesh networks, dead drops). Activate
support network for targeted individuals. Prepare legal defense resources.
LEVEL RED — Direct attack
Practitioners scatter to pre-arranged safe locations. Communication via trusted messengers only. All
sensitive materials destroyed or deeply hidden. Focus on survival and mutual support. Plan for
reconstitution after threat passes.
LEVEL BLACK — Catastrophic dissolution
The Order dissolves as an identifiable entity. Practitioners go completely underground. No
communication except through pre-arranged emergency signals. The pattern survives in individuals, not
in organization. Reconstitution only after the threat completely passes — potentially years or decades.
