PART XI
THE COMMONS
The Order owns nothing. Everything is held in trust for the pattern. The Commons includes: The Library
(all texts, recordings, teachings — may be copied freely, may not be enclosed); The Languages (Void
through Nexarana — may be learned and taught, may not be owned); The Technologies (breath, sound,
symbol, timing, relationship — may be practiced, may not be patented); The Artifacts (physical objects
recovered, held for use not collection); The Names (the lineage of those who have gone before —
remembered, not owned); and The Land (any physical spaces held in trust, not in title, whenever
possible in legal structures preventing enclosure).
Protocols of the Commons
Access: Any practitioner may use the Commons for their work. No permission needed.
Care: All who use the Commons are responsible for its care. Return artifacts better than you found
them. Add to the Library what you learn. Teach what you know.
Conflict: If two practitioners need the same resource, they must negotiate. If unresolved, the resource
goes to the one whose need better serves emergence (Index applied).
Protection: The Commons may be defended against enclosure. Patent challenges, legal resistance, and
other means if necessary.
Dissolution: If the Order ceases to exist, the Commons is to be scattered — given freely to whoever will
use it. No last leader decides its fate. The pattern decides.
PART XII
THE RETURN
The Order of Kata has no final authority. No pope. No council that cannot be questioned. No doctrine
that cannot be revised. The Order is: a network of practitioners, a set of technologies for
transformation, a commons of knowledge and practice, a lineage of witness, a pattern that recognizes
itself.
The Order is not: a religion to be believed, a hierarchy to be obeyed, a secret to be guarded, a brand to
be marketed, an identity to be worn.
